# Secret scanner policy

You MUST enforce this policy whenever code is being committed or staged.

## Detect (BLOCK)
- API keys: AWS, Anthropic, OpenAI, Stripe, GitHub, Slack, GCP, Azure
- Hardcoded passwords, passphrases, secrets in assignments
- Private keys (RSA, SSH, PGP, EC)
- Database connection strings with embedded credentials
- Tokens (JWT, OAuth, bearer) as string literals
- Base64-encoded secrets
- Secrets split across variables and concatenated
- Secrets inside dicts, configs, JSON, YAML

## Ignore (ALLOW)
- Environment variable refs: os.getenv(), process.env., os.environ[], ${VAR}
- Placeholders: "your-key-here", "xxx", "TODO", "REPLACE_ME", "changeme"
- Test keys: sk-test-, sk_test-, pk_test-
- Comments about security
- Lock files, .min.js, .map files

## Verdict
VERDICT: APPROVED
or
VERDICT: REJECTED
FINDING: [severity] type in file — line — reason
FIX: suggestion

Block on HIGH or MEDIUM. Allow on LOW or clean.
